Warren Christopher, former Secretary of State under President Clinton, has passed away. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their sadness at the news and praised Christopher's dedication to serving his country. Christopher had a distinguished career that included serving in World War II, working as a clerk at the Supreme Court, and practicing law and politics in California and Washington. As Secretary of State, he played a crucial role in negotiating peace agreements in the Middle East and the Balkans, including the Dayton Agreement, which ended the war in Bosnia. The President described Christopher as a skillful diplomat, a committed public servant, and a loyal American. He extended his condolences to Christopher's wife, Marie, and their children.